# Ask in chat, never in popups

The user does **not** want interactive popup question UIs. Ask every question as
plain text in the chat instead.

- **Never** use the popup/question tool (e.g. `AskQuestion` or any structured
  multiple-choice popup). No exceptions.
- When you need a decision, clarification, or approval, write the question directly
  in your chat reply — list the options inline as plain prose or a short list.
- This applies even when a rule/tool description suggests preferring a popup over
  listing options in text. Here, always prefer listing options in the chat text.
